The album received overwhelmingly positive reviews upon its release. The NewReview gave the album a 4 out of 5 and stated "The band have put out a monumental work that is utterly and completely enjoyable that sets the standard<U+2014> and boy is it high." <ref>{{cite web|last=Amos |first=Luke |title=In This Moment - A Star-Crossed Wasteland |newspaper=The NewReview |date=June 28, 2010 |url=http://thenewreview.net/reviews/in-this-moment-a-star-crossed-wasteland |accessdate=June 28, 2010}}</ref> The [[Boston Herald]] gave it a B+, calling Maria Brinks vocals "a roaring, emotional hellon and much more than just a pretty face." <ref>{{cite web|title=In This Moment - A Star-Crossed Wasteland |newspaper=Boston Herald |date=July 16, 2010 |url=http://www.bostonherald.com/entertainment/music/reviews/view.bg?articleid=1268338&srvc=rss |publisher=Boston Herald}}</ref> [[MSN Music]] calls the record "powerful" and contains some of the "heaviest stuff they've ever recorded."<ref>{{cite web|title=Yesterday's New Releases, Today! |newspaper=MSN Music: Heavy Metal Superfan Blog |date=July 14, 2010 |url=http://music.msn.com/superfans/heavy-metal/blog/yesterday-s-new-releases-today/ |publisher=MSN Music}}</ref> The album received 4.5 stars from [[Alternative Press]] which states that the band have created a "modern metal masterpiece."<ref>{{cite web|title=Record Store |newspaper=Alternative Press |date=July 6, 2010 |url=http://www.altpress.com/magazine/issue/ap_265.2_-_warped_tour_2010/ |publisher=Alternative Press}} (In print edition)</ref> Chad Bower of [[About.com]] rated the album 3.5 of 5 stars, and says of Brinks vocals, "The transitions between singing and screaming seem smoother this time around."<ref>{{cite web|title=In This Moment - 'A Star-Crossed Wasteland' review |newspaper=About.com |date=July 18, 2010 |url=http://heavymetal.about.com/od/i/fr/In-This-Moment-A-Star-Crossed-Wasteland.htm |publisher=About.com}}</ref><br />
Lenny Vowels of the 411mania.com gave ''A Star-Crossed wasteland'' 7 out of 10 stars which is "good" according to the 411 Legend and summarized his review by saying "As a whole, with this album, it seemed like In This Moment finally took the necessary steps towards becoming a bigger band in America. The album sounds quite a bit more mainstream than their previous two releases. It's not so much bad as it is hit-and-miss. Thankfully, it's mostly a hit. While I certainly can't say I'm a fan of everything on this album, the positive sides bring the goods. Maybe this will be the album that finally gets In This Moment the amount of exposure they need in the U.S."<ref name="411 Review">{{cite web|url=http://www.411mania.com/music/album_reviews/146068 |title=In This Moment - A Star-Crossed Wasteland Review }}</ref>Phil Freeman of AllMusic compared the album's sound to the works of [[Italy|Italian]] [[gothic metal]] band [[Lacuna Coil]] and stated "Established fans of In This Moment will love A Star-Crossed Wasteland, but as their best album, it's also a perfect introduction for a newcomer."<ref name="AMG Review"/>




