==Chart Positions and Sales==
''A Star-Crossed Wasteland'' debuted at #40 on the [[Billboard 200]], selling approximately 10,500 copies in its first week of release.<ref>{{cite web|title=IN THIS MOMENT's 'A Star-Crossed Wasteland' Cracks U.S. Top 40  |newspaper=Blabbermouth |date=July 21, 2010 |url=http://www.roadrunnerrecords.com/blabbermouth.net/news.aspx?mode=Article&newsitemID=143295 |accessdate=July 21, 2010}}</ref>It also debuted at #1 on the Billboard Independent albums chart and #8 on the Top Hard Rock albums chart.<ref name="Billboard Charts"/> This is the highest chart position to date by the band beating its [[The Dream (In This Moment album)|predecessor]] which debuted at #70 on the Billboard 200 with 8,000 copies sold in 2008.

